{
  "id": "intunewin32appuninstall",
  "name": "IntuneWin32AppUninstall",
  "description": "IntuneWin32AppUninstall is a PowerShell GUI tool that inventories MSI-based apps by scanning uninstall registry keys (HKLM and HKCU) and generates Intune-compatible detection and remediation scripts. For each selected app it creates a ready-to-deploy package with Detect and Remediate scripts, a README, and AppInfo.json, with batch generation, per-app folders, and CSV export. Remediation uninstalls silently via msiexec /X {GUID} and logs results for Intune deployment under Endpoint Security.",
